review: Dr Sankalp Bali is very experienced doctor **** ******** ******* ********* ** ***** He is friendly and gives the detail about your problems in depth. Actually i was doing go karting then after few mins  i was rounding a bend when the grip on the tyres of the kart did not seem adequate causing me to skid , spin out of control and hit a stack of tyres surrounding the track. I felt immediate pain in my chest due to the kart crash. My upper front teeth injured my lower lips  . Next day i felt difficulty in breathing and pain during hiccups i could not even sleep properly so i went to Diagnostic centre for my immediate x rays and got my report as well . Report said all normal then i was relaxed . But there was no regular pain . Pain used to have only wen i used to wake up i used to sleep and during hiccups . So i thought to consult a doctor and i googled to search for some good doctors online  so Dr Sankalp Bali was my first choice. I went up there and there were more patients sitting up . I had to wait but it was worth waiting. He got into the root of my problem and wrote a treatment plan . I recommend him for all kind of patients visit him and get an advice . Bcoz just a single good advice can change your health and life. Doctors like him is much needed in our society. Thanku doc .

review: I got sudden unbearable pain in iliac crest which was unbearable. Due to the pandemic issue we were scared of going to any hospital. I found Dr Bali on Practo. For a patient it is really important that someone should listen them carefully which doctors usually dont  . But trust me after talking to Dr. Bali I felt relaxed. I am having medicines prescribed, hoping for the best outcome. Thanks a lot and loads of gratitude n respect to the doctor . It is already difficult times everyone going through , I really thanks doctor for listening me .

review: Happy with diagnose procedure, but unsatisfied with the explanation on the problem. Nothing has happen anyways, there are certain reason.
reply_text:
Dear Patient, 

              Short duration pain in muscle and joints can occur many a time without any disease or pathology. The causative factors may include- anxiety, weather change, lack of exercise, viamin D deficiency, food allergy, seasonal allergy, cigarettes, alcohol, obesity, depression etc. Many a time it is not possible to pin-point the exact cause of short duration pain.

                                                       Dr Sankalp Bali
